cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.DC

This paper discusses the Medium Access Control (MAC) protocol for Wireless Local Area Networks (WLANs) and its ability to perform traffic differentiation. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper also discusses the performance evaluation of the protocol under different traffic conditions, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also mentions the management of multiple queues and virtual collisions, which could be related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
